comments: Tatum (BOS) makes clean contact with the ball and temporarily dislodges it away from Highsmith (MIA).
Brown (BOS) slightly extends his arms as he engages with Adebayo (MIA) and marginal contact occurs before Adebayo sets the pick.
Robinson (MIA) wraps his arm around White (BOS) as he approaches and goes over the pick. The illegal contact by Robinson occurs prior to any contact by Tatum (BOS) during the pick.
During the inbound, Adebayo (MIA) immediately slides his hand off of Porzingis' (BOS) body and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Robinson (MIA) and White (BOS) mutually engage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Tatum (BOS) briefly grasps and immediately releases Robinson's (MIA) arm as marginal contact occurs off-ball.

Tatum (BOS) leans forward and extends toward Robinson's (MIA) at the start of the drive, as a result Robinson's arm makes marginal contact to Tatum's head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Tatum (BOS) establishes his left foot as his pivot and maintains it prior to the shot attempt.
Robinson (MIA) brushes Tatum's (BOS) arm and marginal contact occurs during Tatum's (BOS) shot attempt near the rim.
The 24 second shot clock expires and the shot attempt does not touch the rim. The expiration of the shot clock occurs prior to any contact during a potential rebound attempt.
While defending Adebayo (MIA) and the pick, Holiday (BOS) walks up the floor with an outstretched arm, Adebayo grabs it and hooks the arm to exaggerate the incidental contact.
Martin (MIA) reaches in and makes illegal contact with Porzingis' (BOS) arm during the pursuit for the rebound.
Tatum (BOS) makes clean contact with the ball and temporarily deflects it away from Adebayo (MIA) during both steal attempts.
Highsmith (MIA) avoids making any illegal contact with Tatum's (BOS) arm as they both pursue the loose ball during the rebound.
Highsmith (MIA) legally contests Brown's (BOS) jump shot attempt.
The ball does not touch the baseline out of bounds after Porzingis (BOS) tips the rebound and Brown (BOS) stays inbounds to legally recover the loose ball.
Adebayo (MIA) and Porzingis (BOS) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Following the inbound, Robinson (MIA) makes contact with Tatum's (BOS) body, affecting his SQBR.
Tatum (BOS) brings his arm toward Herro's (MIA) path and marginal contact occurs with Herro's body during the drive and shot attempt.
The Boston Celtics are granted a timeout while Jaquez Jr. (MIA) applies defensive pressure and makes marginal arm contact with Tatum (BOS).
